gacy of ethnic gerrymandering incites conflict even now.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aIntriguexPolitical aspectszKyrgyzstanxHistoryy21st century. 0aIntriguexPolitical aspectszUzbekistanxHistoryy21st century. 0aRevolutionszKyrgyzstanxHistoryy21st century. 0aRevolutionszUzbekistanxHistoryy21st century. 0aViolencezKyrgyzstanxHistoryy21st century. 0aViolencezUzbekistanxHistoryy21st century. 7aHISTORY / Asia / Central Asia.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018598040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300185980423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300185980/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec2000d2014  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles